Run the program installer as root:

sudo ./installer

It runs apt to install several packages. It will put starter scripts for 
wax and waxconfig in /usr/local/bin.

It puts the theme in ~/.themes.

It creates a virtual environment in ~/.venv.

It appends an alias va to .bash_aliases. Use it to activate the virtual
environment.

When the installer finishes, type "wax" to run wax.

